Sentencas: The layered SmBa0.5Sr0.5Co2O5+delta (SBSC) perovskite oxide is synthesized by the Pechini method and investigated as a novel cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: High performance layered SmBa0.5Sr0.5Co2O5+δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A laboratory-sized Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC)-based tri-layer cell of NiO-SDC/SDC/SBSC is operated from 500 to 700 degrees C fed with humidified H-2 (similar to 3% H2O) as a fuel and the static ambient air as oxidant.
Titulo: High performance layered SmBa0.5Sr0.5Co2O5+δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A maximum power density of 1147 mW cm(-2) is achieved at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: High performance layered SmBa0.5Sr0.5Co2O5+δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The interfacial polarization resistance is as low as 1.01, 0.38, 0.16, 0.06 and 0.03 Omega cm(2) at 500, 550, 600, 650 and 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: High performance layered SmBa0.5Sr0.5Co2O5+δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The experimental results indicate that SBSC is a very promising cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: High performance layered SmBa0.5Sr0.5Co2O5+δ cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
